Package: diamondback
Title: Fast Patch-Based Analysis of Very Large Categorical Rasters
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Gates", "Dupont", , "dupont97@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Connected-component labelling, patch metrics, core-area
    calculation and temporal patch lineage analysis for categorical and binary
    rasters with hundreds of millions of cells. Raster input/output, geometry
    and validation stay in R via 'terra'; the array kernels are delegated to
    NumPy and SciPy through 'reticulate', which is typically far faster than
    pure-R connected-component labelling on large grids. Includes explicit
    handling of missing values and study-area masks, memory estimation before
    allocation, result caching keyed on input fingerprints, and validation of
    results against independent checks.
